This is first day in terraform-aws tutorial with hands on and theory

> this is conducted on gnu/linux-ubuntu distro
> pre-requisites understanding of aws provider services and familiarity with its elements
> aws already configured
> terraform already configured with repository and gnu key
> this tutorial/hands on involves launching aws resources so relevent aws iam account for resource access is necessary
> terraform lifecycle management and statefile management

my-terraform-project/
├── modules/
│   ├── VPC/
│   │   ├── main.tf
│   │   ├── variables.tf
│   │   └── outputs.tf
│   └── ec2_instance/
│       ├── main.tf
│       ├── variables.tf
│       └── outputs.tf
└── environments/
    ├── dev/
    │   ├── main.tf
    │   ├── variables.tf
    │   ├── outputs.tf
    │   ├── providers.tf
    │   └── terraform.tfvars
    ├── staging/
    │   ├── main.tf
    │   ├── variables.tf
    │   ├── outputs.tf
    │   ├── providers.tf
    │   └── terraform.tfvars
    └── prod/
        ├── main.tf
        ├── variables.tf
        ├── outputs.tf
        ├── providers.tf
        └── terraform.tfvars
